    "overview": {
      "id": "overview",
      "name": "Product Overview",
      "content": "<h2>What is IdiamPro?</h2><p>IdiamPro is your <strong>second brain — with profound capabilities</strong>. It's an AI-native outlining platform that doesn't just store your knowledge — it actively helps you think. Import your research from any source, and IdiamPro synthesizes it into structured, integrated knowledge, just as a researcher synthesizes hundreds or even thousands of sources into a knowledge base that can be used to draw original conclusions.</p><p>Most knowledge tools are passive — they hold what you put in. IdiamPro is active. It synthesizes your sources, generates content that builds on your existing structure, and lets you work at a scale that would be unmanageable manually. We call each IdiamPro outline a <strong>Knowledge Molecule</strong> — a living, structured entity that folds and unfolds like DNA, growing as you learn and expressing only what you need in the moment.</p><h3>Core Capabilities</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Hierarchical Thinking:</strong> Structure any project as a navigable outline with unlimited depth</p></li><li><p><strong>AI at Every Node:</strong> Generate contextually-aware content that understands your full document structure</p></li><li><p><strong>Built-in Research Assistant:</strong> Import and synthesize content from PDFs, YouTube, web pages, audio, and more into integrated knowledge</p></li><li><p><strong>Scale Without Limits:</strong> Handle massive documents (66,000+ nodes) with smooth performance</p></li><li><p><strong>Cross-Platform:</strong> Work seamlessly across Mac, iOS, and web today — with Windows and Linux Electron builds configured and Android via Capacitor on the roadmap</p></li></ul><h3>Who Is It For?</h3><ul><li><p>Writers and authors</p></li><li><p>Researchers and academics</p></li><li><p>Business professionals</p></li><li><p>Knowledge workers</p></li><li><p>Content creators</p></li><li><p>Consultants and strategists</p></li></ul><p></p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root",
      "childrenIds": [
        "concept-idea-incubator",
        "overview-differentiators",
        "overview-second-brain",
        "overview-testimonials"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "1"
    },
    "overview-differentiators": {
      "id": "overview-differentiators",
      "name": "Key Differentiators",
      "content": "<h3>Why IdiamPro vs. Other Tools?</h3><h4>Compared to Traditional Outliners</h4><ul><li><p><strong>Unlimited depth:</strong> Most outliners limit how many levels deep you can go. IdiamPro has no limits — nest as deep as you need.</p></li><li><p><strong>Built-in AI:</strong> Traditional outliners have no AI. IdiamPro generates content that understands your entire document.</p></li><li><p><strong>Import anything:</strong> Other outliners require manual copy-paste. IdiamPro pulls in PDFs, YouTube videos, audio, and web pages automatically.</p></li><li><p><strong>Handles massive documents:</strong> Other tools slow down at a few thousand items. IdiamPro handles 66,000+ without breaking a sweat.</p></li><li><p><strong>Built-in research assistant:</strong> IdiamPro doesn't just store your sources — it works like a research assistant. Pull in PDFs, YouTube videos, audio recordings, web pages, and existing outlines, and AI synthesizes them into a single integrated outline that weaves together the knowledge from all your sources. Think of how a PhD student synthesizes dozens of papers into a thesis, or how a researcher integrates findings across studies — IdiamPro does that for you automatically.</p></li><li><p><strong>Universal knowledge unification:</strong> Your knowledge is scattered everywhere — AI conversations spread across ChatGPT, Claude, and Gemini; research trapped in PDFs; insights buried in YouTube videos, audio recordings, web pages, and Google Docs. IdiamPro is the first tool that unifies all of these sources into a single, structured knowledge base. Capture highlights from any LLM, import documents in any format, and AI synthesizes everything together in context. One place for all your knowledge, no matter where it originated.</p></li></ul><h4>Compared to AI Writing Tools</h4><ul><li><p><strong>Structure-aware:</strong> AI writing tools treat your document as one flat block of text. IdiamPro's AI understands your outline hierarchy and writes content that fits.</p></li><li><p><strong>No length limits:</strong> AI writing tools hit token limits on long documents. IdiamPro works with documents of any size.</p></li><li><p><strong>Private AI option:</strong> AI writing tools send everything to the cloud. IdiamPro can run AI entirely on your own computer — your data never leaves your machine.</p></li></ul><p></p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "overview",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "1.1"
    },
    "overview-second-brain": {
      "id": "overview-second-brain",
      "name": "Your Second Brain — With Profound Capabilities",
      "content": "<h3>IdiamPro as a Second Brain</h3><p>The \"second brain\" concept (popularized by Tiago Forte's <em>Building a Second Brain</em> methodology) is about capturing, organizing, distilling, and expressing knowledge. IdiamPro does all four — but goes far beyond what typical tools in this space offer.</p><h4>What typical second brain tools do (Notion, Obsidian, Roam)</h4><ul><li>Capture and store notes</li><li>Link ideas together</li><li>Search and retrieve</li></ul><h4>What IdiamPro adds</h4><ul><li><strong>AI that synthesizes your knowledge</strong> — not just stores it. IdiamPro actively helps you think by connecting and integrating ideas across your entire document.</li><li><strong>Multi-source import:</strong> Pull in PDFs, YouTube videos, audio recordings, web pages, and existing outlines automatically — no manual copy-paste.</li><li><strong>Hierarchical structure:</strong> Mirrors how people naturally think about complex topics, with unlimited nesting depth.</li><li><strong>Context-aware content generation:</strong> AI writes content that understands the full context of your knowledge base, not just the current page.</li><li><strong>Massive scale:</strong> Handle 66,000+ items without slowing down — far beyond what other tools can manage.</li></ul><h4>A Living Outline — The Knowledge Molecule</h4><p>Think of your IdiamPro outline like a DNA molecule. DNA contains your entire genetic code, but at any moment only specific genes are unfolded and expressed — the rest stays compactly coiled, ready when needed. Your IdiamPro outline works the same way. Your full second brain holds everything — all your knowledge, all your sources, all your ideas — but you expand only the areas you're actively working with and collapse everything else. When your focus shifts, you fold one area closed and unfold another.</p><p>This is why we call an IdiamPro outline a <strong>Knowledge Molecule</strong>. It's not a static document — it's a living, structured entity that contains your entire knowledge base while expressing only what you need right now. Like DNA, it grows, adapts, and organizes complexity into something you can work with.</p><p>This isn't just an organizational trick. It's what makes it possible to work with a knowledge base of thousands of items without feeling overwhelmed. You're never looking at everything at once — you're looking at exactly what's relevant right now, with the full context of everything else one click away.</p><p><strong>An IdiamPro outline is a living thing.</strong> It grows as you learn. It adapts as your focus changes. It holds the full complexity of your knowledge while showing you only what you need in the moment — just like DNA expresses only the genes the cell needs right now, while keeping the entire genome intact and ready.</p><h4>Capture Ideas When They Come</h4><p>Working on one thing and an idea hits you for something else? Drop it into your outline right where it belongs. IdiamPro holds the context so you don't have to — your second brain remembers it, and you can pick it up later without losing your train of thought. That's what a second brain is for: letting you think freely without worrying about losing ideas.</p><h4>The Key Difference</h4><p>Most second brain tools are <strong>passive</strong> — they hold what you put in. IdiamPro is <strong>active</strong>. It synthesizes your sources, generates content that builds on your existing structure, and lets you work at a scale that would be unmanageable manually. It's not just a place to store knowledge — it's a research assistant that synthesizes hundreds or even thousands of sources into a knowledge base you can use to draw original conclusions.</p><p>That's what makes a Knowledge Molecule different from an ordinary outline. It's alive — it grows, folds, unfolds, and evolves with your thinking.</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "overview",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "1.2"
    },
    "overview-testimonials": {
      "id": "overview-testimonials",
      "name": "Testimonials (To Collect)",
      "content": "<h3>We Built This With IdiamPro</h3><p>This website was generated from an IdiamPro outline. We maintain our marketing knowledge base in IdiamPro — product positioning, features, workflows, pricing — and the website is generated directly from it. When we update the outline, the website updates.</p><p>This isn't just how we work — it's a model for how you can work too. Maintain your knowledge in IdiamPro and let it become your website, your documentation, your training materials, or any other output you need.</p><h3>Testimonials (Coming Soon)</h3><p><em>Collecting quotes from beta users focusing on:</em></p><ul><li><p>Time saved on research synthesis</p></li><li><p>Quality of AI-generated content</p></li><li><p>Ability to handle large documents</p></li><li><p>Cross-platform workflow</p></li><li><p>Unifying knowledge from multiple AI chatbots and sources</p></li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "overview",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "1.3"
    },
    "platforms": {
      "id": "platforms",
      "name": "Platform Support",
      "content": "<h2>Available Platforms</h2><p>IdiamPro runs natively on multiple platforms with feature parity where possible.</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root",
      "childrenIds": [
        "platforms-current",
        "platforms-future",
        "platforms-comparison"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "2"
    },
    "platforms-current": {
      "id": "platforms-current",
      "name": "Currently Available",
      "content": "<h3>macOS (Desktop App)</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Technology:</strong> Electron app, distributed as a .dmg installer</p></li><li><p><strong>Architecture:</strong> Universal binary — works on both Apple Silicon and Intel Macs</p></li><li><p><strong>Features:</strong> Full feature set including Ollama integration (private AI) and native file system access</p></li><li><p><strong>Minimum OS:</strong> macOS 11 (Big Sur) or later</p></li></ul><h3>iOS / iPadOS (Mobile)</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Technology:</strong> Native app built with Capacitor, distributed via the App Store</p></li><li><p><strong>Features:</strong> Full feature set with touch-optimized gestures and native share sheet</p></li><li><p><strong>Minimum OS:</strong> iOS 15 or later</p></li></ul><h3>Web Browser</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Supported:</strong> Chrome, Edge, Safari, and Firefox</p></li><li><p>No installation needed — just open in your browser</p></li><li><p>Chrome and Edge provide the best experience thanks to the File System Access API, which lets you save files directly to your computer</p></li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "platforms",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "2.1"
    },
    "platforms-future": {
      "id": "platforms-future",
      "name": "Future Platforms (Roadmap)",
      "content": "<h3>Coming Soon</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Windows:</strong> Electron app with NSIS installer + portable version</p></li><li><p><strong>Linux:</strong> Available as AppImage and DEB packages</p></li><li><p><strong>Android:</strong> Built with Capacitor, distributed via Google Play Store</p></li></ul><h3>Under Consideration</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Chrome Extension:</strong> Quick capture — grab ideas from any web page</p></li><li><p><strong>VS Code Extension:</strong> Integration for software developers</p></li><li><p><strong>Obsidian Plugin:</strong> Connect with the popular knowledge management app</p></li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "platforms",
      "childrenIds": [
        "platforms-android-work"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "2.2"
    },
    "platforms-android-work": {
      "id": "platforms-android-work",
      "name": "Android — Work Required",
      "content": "<h3>Android Port — What's Needed</h3><p>Since IdiamPro already uses Capacitor for iOS, the core web app and most bridge code carry over. Android is the easiest future platform to add, but still requires dedicated work:</p><ol><li><strong>UI testing and fixes:</strong> Android has different screen sizes, navigation patterns, and back button behavior that need attention</li><li><strong>Touch gesture tuning:</strong> Android and iOS handle touch events slightly differently — swipe gestures will need calibration</li><li><strong>Storage layer:</strong> Android has its own file system conventions that need to be implemented</li><li><strong>App Store packaging:</strong> Google Play Store submission, APK/AAB signing, store listing, and screenshots</li><li><strong>Platform-specific bug fixes:</strong> There are always device- and OS-specific issues to resolve</li></ol><p><strong>Advantage:</strong> The Capacitor infrastructure is already in place from the iOS build. This gives us a significant head start — the architecture is already cross-platform.</p>",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "platforms-future",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "2.2.1"
    },
    "platforms-comparison": {
      "id": "platforms-comparison",
      "name": "Platform Feature Comparison",
      "content": "<h3>What Works Where</h3><p><strong>Available everywhere</strong> (Mac, iPhone/iPad, Web, and coming to Windows, Linux, and Android):</p><ul><li>All outlining features</li><li>AI content generation</li><li>PDF, YouTube, and web page import</li><li>Audio transcription</li><li>Keyboard shortcuts (partial on iPhone/iPad)</li></ul><p><strong>Desktop only</strong> (Mac, and coming to Windows and Linux):</p><ul><li>Private AI (runs AI on your own computer, no internet needed)</li><li>Full file system access (save anywhere on your computer)</li></ul><p><strong>iPhone, iPad, and Android (coming soon):</strong></p><ul><li>Touch gestures (swipe to indent/outdent, drag to reorganize) — these same actions are performed via keyboard shortcuts (Tab, Shift+Tab, drag) on desktop and web</li></ul><p><em>Windows, Linux, and Android versions coming soon</em></p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "platforms",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "2.3"
    },
    "requirements": {
      "id": "requirements",
      "name": "System Requirements",
      "content": "<h2>Technical Requirements</h2><p>Minimum and recommended specifications for running IdiamPro.</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root",
      "childrenIds": [
        "req-macos",
        "req-ios",
        "req-web",
        "req-optional"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": true,
      "prefix": "3"
    },
    "req-macos": {
      "id": "req-macos",
      "name": "macOS Requirements",
      "content": "<h3>Minimum Requirements</h3><ul><li><strong>OS:</strong> macOS 11.0 (Big Sur) or later</li><li><strong>Processor:</strong> Intel Core i5 or Apple M1</li><li><strong>RAM:</strong> 4 GB</li><li><strong>Storage:</strong> 500 MB for application</li><li><strong>Internet:</strong> Required for AI features (unless using private AI)</li></ul><h3>Recommended</h3><ul><li><strong>OS:</strong> macOS 13.0 (Ventura) or later</li><li><strong>Processor:</strong> Apple M1 or later</li><li><strong>RAM:</strong> 8 GB+ (16 GB for large outlines)</li><li><strong>Storage:</strong> SSD with 2 GB+ free space</li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "requirements",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3.1"
    },
    "req-ios": {
      "id": "req-ios",
      "name": "iOS Requirements",
      "content": "<h3>Minimum Requirements</h3><ul><li><strong>OS:</strong> iOS 15.0 or later</li><li><strong>Device:</strong> iPhone 8 or later, iPad (6th gen) or later</li><li><strong>Storage:</strong> 200 MB for application</li><li><strong>Internet:</strong> Required for AI features</li></ul><h3>Recommended</h3><ul><li><strong>OS:</strong> iOS 17.0 or later</li><li><strong>Device:</strong> iPhone 12 or later, iPad Pro</li><li><strong>Storage:</strong> 1 GB+ free for outline storage</li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "requirements",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3.2"
    },
    "req-web": {
      "id": "req-web",
      "name": "Web Browser Requirements",
      "content": "<h3>Supported Browsers</h3><ul><li><strong>Chrome:</strong> Version 100 or later (recommended)</li><li><strong>Edge:</strong> Version 100 or later</li><li><strong>Safari:</strong> Version 15 or later</li><li><strong>Firefox:</strong> Version 100 or later</li></ul><h3>Notes</h3><ul><li>Chrome and Edge offer the best experience — they let you save files directly to your computer</li><li>Your browser must allow cookies and local storage so your work is saved</li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "requirements",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3.3"
    },
    "req-optional": {
      "id": "req-optional",
      "name": "Optional Components",
      "content": "<h3>Ollama with Gemma 4 — Private, Offline AI (Optional, Multimodal)</h3><p>Ollama with Gemma 4 lets you run AI entirely on your own computer (now multimodal — supports text and images) — nothing is sent to the cloud. Install it and IdiamPro connects automatically.</p><ul><li><strong>Download:</strong> <a href=\"https://ollama.ai\">ollama.ai</a></li><li><strong>RAM:</strong> 8 GB minimum (16 GB recommended)</li><li><strong>Storage:</strong> 4–8 GB per model</li><li><strong>Recommended models:</strong><ul><li><code>llama3.2</code> — Best balance of speed and quality (default)</li><li><code>phi3</code> — Fastest responses, lighter weight</li><li><code>llama3.1</code> — Highest quality output</li><li><code>codellama</code> — Optimized for code-related tasks</li></ul></li></ul><h3>AssemblyAI — Audio Transcription (Optional)</h3><p>Converts audio and video recordings to text, with speaker diarization (identifies who said what).</p><ul><li>Sign up at <a href=\"https://www.assemblyai.com\">assemblyai.com</a> and add your API key to IdiamPro's settings</li><li>Free tier: 100 hours/month for testing</li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "requirements",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "3.4"
    },
    "features": {
      "id": "features",
      "name": "Features & Capabilities",
      "content": "<h2>Complete Feature Set</h2><p>IdiamPro combines powerful outlining with AI-native capabilities.</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root",
      "childrenIds": [
        "feat-outlining",
        "feat-ai",
        "feat-import",
        "feat-export",
        "feat-organization",
