    "feat-multimedia-shipped-2026-06-11": {
      "id": "feat-multimedia-shipped-2026-06-11",
      "name": "Multimedia AI shipped (2026-06-11)",
      "content": "<p><strong>Previously planned for v1.1 — now shipping in v1.</strong></p><p><strong>1. Capture from image.</strong> Take a photo of any whiteboard, mind map, or sticky-note brainstorm — IdiamPro extracts a structured outline from it. Hand-drawn diagrams, sticky-note storms, slide screenshots, textbook pages — all turn into editable hierarchies in seconds. Three-panel preview lets you edit names before committing. Available on every platform; iOS adds a native camera button.</p><p><strong>2. Share as YouTube package.</strong> Turn any chapter of an outline into a complete YouTube content package: voiceover script with shot markers, chapter list, description, 5 title variants, SEO tags, thumbnail concept, B-roll prompts ready for Runway / MagicLight / Sora, and a screen-recording shot list. Export as markdown or save as a new outline.</p><p><strong>Why it matters for positioning:</strong> 'Outliner that turns your napkin sketch into a YouTube script' is a sharper differentiator than any of the original v1 messaging. Both features fit the 'Premier Idea Developer' tagline directly — capture an idea, develop it, ship it.</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "root",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": ""
    },
    "agentic-processes-marketing-2026-06-11": {
      "id": "agentic-processes-marketing-2026-06-11",
      "name": "Agentic Workflows (Future)",
      "content": "<h3>Agentic Workflows</h3><p>Coming after launch as a future capability. IdiamPro's AI tools today produce one output at a time — reformat a node, translate an outline, refresh from the web, capture an outline from an image. The next step is chaining these into multi-step autonomous workflows: research → synthesize → outline → derivative outline → video package, with you supervising rather than driving each step.</p><p><em>Not committing to a specific date — capability is on the roadmap, dates will firm up after v1 launch settles.</em></p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "roadmap",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "9.3"
    },
    "concept-idea-incubator-capture": {
      "id": "concept-idea-incubator-capture",
      "name": "Capture",
      "content": "<p>Drop in anything, no matter how rough. A 2am thought, a YouTube video, a dense PDF, a voice memo.</p>",
      "type": "text",
      "parentId": "concept-idea-incubator",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": ""
    },
    "concept-idea-incubator-structure": {
      "id": "concept-idea-incubator-structure",
      "name": "Structure",
      "content": "<p>Watch chaos become an outline you can shape, expand, and rearrange.</p>",
      "type": "text",
      "parentId": "concept-idea-incubator",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": ""
    },
    "concept-idea-incubator-enrich": {
      "id": "concept-idea-incubator-enrich",
      "name": "Enrich",
      "content": "<p>Refresh any part against the live web so your thinking never goes stale, and ask your own outlines questions.</p>",
      "type": "text",
      "parentId": "concept-idea-incubator",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": ""
    },
    "concept-idea-incubator-hatch": {
      "id": "concept-idea-incubator-hatch",
      "name": "Hatch",
      "content": "<p>When an idea is ready, generate the finished thing: a document, a script, a podcast, a content package.</p>",
      "type": "text",
      "parentId": "concept-idea-incubator",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": ""
    },
    "concept-idea-incubator": {
      "id": "concept-idea-incubator",
      "name": "The Idea Incubator (core concept)",
      "content": "<p><strong>Definition:</strong> An Idea Incubator is where raw thoughts grow into finished work.</p><p>Most tools store your notes. An Idea Incubator does something different — it takes the scattered raw material of your thinking (half-formed thoughts, saved videos, PDFs, web pages, meeting scraps) and actively grows them into structured, usable ideas.</p><p>The four stages: Capture → Structure → Enrich → Hatch.</p><p><strong>Closing line:</strong> That's the difference between a filing cabinet and an incubator. One stores your ideas. The other helps them grow up.</p><p><em>Shipped to the marketing/landing page as the lead concept section (right after the hero).</em></p>",
      "type": "text",
      "parentId": "overview",
      "childrenIds": [
        "concept-idea-incubator-capture",
        "concept-idea-incubator-structure",
        "concept-idea-incubator-enrich",
        "concept-idea-incubator-hatch"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": ""
    },
    "sub-ownit": {
      "id": "sub-ownit",
      "name": "Own it — $29.99 one-time ($19.99 founder launch)",
      "content": "<h3>Own it — One-Time Purchase</h3><p><strong>Price:</strong> $29.99 one-time — <strong>$19.99 founder launch price</strong> for the first cohort. Buy it once, own it forever. No subscription.</p><h4>What You Get</h4><ul><li>All the core outlining and second-brain features — unlimited outlines, all item types, the full editor, import, export, and multi-platform (Mac, iPhone, web).</li><li><strong>Private on-device AI (Ollama / Gemma)</strong> — runs on your own computer, no key needed, unlimited.</li><li><strong>A capped free-cloud AI allowance</strong> — enough to get real work done for the core features.</li><li><strong>Bring your own key (BYOK)</strong> — plug in your own AI key for unlimited cloud AI; you pay your provider directly.</li></ul><h4>Why One-Time Works Here</h4><p>The entry tier's AI is local, capped-free, or your-own-key — so it costs IdiamPro almost nothing to run. That's what makes an honest buy-once, no-subscription price sustainable.</p><h4>When to Step Up to Pro</h4><p>Pro (recurring) sits <strong>above</strong> Own it. Choose Pro when you want premium cloud LLMs, heavy features (podcast/image generation, big-context Refresh/Transform), and higher or unlimited AI caps. Own it covers the essentials; Pro is for power and premium cloud AI.</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "subscriptions",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "7.2"
    },
    "d30bb7de-1ab0-4455-8d5b-67b7d32417a2": {
      "id": "d30bb7de-1ab0-4455-8d5b-67b7d32417a2",
      "name": "Data Safety &amp; Trust — “Your data is safe with us” website copy",
      "content": "<p><strong>Your data is safe with us</strong></p><p><em>IdiamPro is built to protect the one thing that matters most — your thinking.</em></p><p><strong>Your outlines live on your device.</strong> Your work is stored locally, on your own machine — not locked away in someone else's cloud. On desktop they're plain files you own: back them up, move them, or keep them entirely offline.</p><p><strong>Your originals stay yours.</strong> When AI rewrites or reshapes an outline, it creates a new copy by default and leaves your original untouched. When a change edits an outline in place, IdiamPro snapshots it first. Either way, the version you started with is always one step from being restored.</p><p><strong>A safety net before AI changes.</strong> IdiamPro automatically snapshots your outline before AI transforms it (on by default), so any AI change is one click from undone.</p><p><strong>Deep, unlimited undo.</strong> A single Undo reverses your edits, moves, deletes, imports, and AI changes — as far back as you need, with no hard limit.</p><p><strong>Built assuming systems can fail.</strong> We design IdiamPro so that if something goes wrong behind the scenes, it's caught and surfaced — not hidden. Automated checks monitor our services and alert us when something needs attention.</p><p><strong>You always know where your data stands.</strong> On-device AI keeps your content entirely on your machine. When you use your own AI key or a paid plan, your content isn't used to train AI models, under your provider's terms. We tell you plainly what every plan does with your data — no fine print.</p>",
      "type": "text",
      "parentId": "root",
      "childrenIds": [
        "44dca01b-1cb5-4f8c-a312-cfbbaf572df3"
      ],
      "prefix": ""
    },
    "44dca01b-1cb5-4f8c-a312-cfbbaf572df3": {
      "id": "44dca01b-1cb5-4f8c-a312-cfbbaf572df3",
      "name": "⚠ Status, backing &amp; guardrails (do not publish without legal sign-off)",
      "content": "<p><strong>STATUS:</strong> Draft approved by Howard 2026-07-06. Every claim above is backed by the automated <em>Marketing Claims Verification</em> test suite (tests/claims-verification-test.js) — the tests will fail if a future code change makes any line untrue.</p><p><strong>⚠ PENDING LEGAL REVIEW before publishing:</strong> the last pillar (“You always know where your data stands”), specifically the “not used to train AI models” statement — that describes a THIRD-PARTY provider's policy we don't control, so a lawyer must bless the exact wording. Same care as the privacy-tier copy.</p><p><strong>GUARDRAILS (do not violate when editing this copy):</strong></p><ul><li>NEVER write a blanket “your data never leaves your device.” Cloud AI features and the Podcast generator send outline content to a provider/our server per the user's plan. Storage is local; AI processing is not.</li><li>Do NOT say “ALL AI transforms default to a new copy” — Translate defaults to replace-in-place (it snapshots first), and Capture-from-image adds items. The wording above is deliberately scoped to be true.</li><li>Avoid absolute guarantees (“we never lose your data”). Frame as concrete practices, which is testable and defensible.</li></ul><p><strong>Placement:</strong> a “trust” section on the homepage or a short dedicated page; pairs with the privacy-tier messaging.</p>",
      "type": "text",
      "parentId": "d30bb7de-1ab0-4455-8d5b-67b7d32417a2",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": ""
    },
    "creator-outreach": {
      "id": "creator-outreach",
      "name": "Creator & Evangelist Outreach List",
      "content": "<h2>Creator &amp; Evangelist Outreach List</h2><p>A researched target list of currently-active AI creators, authors, and outlets whose audiences are already pre-sold on \"AI can create amazing things.\" Feeds an outreach + beta-invite + (later, with consent) testimonial pipeline. Company: SecondBrainWare LLC. Research date: mid-July 2026.</p>",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "root",
      "childrenIds": [
        "creator-outreach-intro",
        "creator-outreach-writing",
        "creator-outreach-video",
        "creator-outreach-explainers",
        "creator-outreach-newsletters",
        "creator-outreach-genre",
        "creator-outreach-visuals",
        "creator-outreach-tools",
        "creator-outreach-priority",
        "creator-outreach-gaps",
        "creator-outreach-email-template-v1"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": true,
      "prefix": "12"
    },
    "creator-outreach-intro": {
      "id": "creator-outreach-intro",
      "name": "Purpose & Approach",
      "content": "<h3>Purpose</h3><p>Reach real, active authors and creators whose audiences already believe AI can create amazing things — the people who would light up at IdiamPro (one outline &rarr; many finished outputs: books, podcasts, narrated videos, diagrams, graphics, screenplays, legal/professional docs).</p><h3>The pipeline</h3><ul><li><strong>Research</strong> — every entry below surfaced via live web search and has a real, valid URL.</li><li><strong>Invite</strong> — bring them into the beta / v1.</li><li><strong>Consented testimonials</strong> — real quotes, only with explicit permission.</li><li><strong>Reciprocal promotion</strong> — creator promotes IdiamPro, we promote the creator.</li></ul><h3>Honesty rules for this list</h3><ul><li>Subscriber/reader numbers are labeled \"approx\" and included <strong>only</strong> where a source stated one. Where no number was verifiable, it is omitted on purpose — do not guess.</li><li>Individual creators (voices/channels) are kept separate from tools/companies (see the last node).</li><li>Two entries are flagged \"confirm handle before outreach.\" Honor those flags.</li><li>Confirm any omitted counts live before any public testimonial use.</li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "creator-outreach",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "12.1"
    },
