    "creator-outreach-tools": {
      "id": "creator-outreach-tools",
      "name": "Tools/Companies — not individual creators",
      "content": "<h3>Separate bucket &mdash; do not confuse with the creators above</h3><p>These appeared repeatedly in searches. Useful as competitive/landscape context or partnership targets &mdash; <strong>not</strong> creator-testimonial targets.</p><ul><li><strong>HeyGen</strong> &mdash; https://www.heygen.com &mdash; AI avatar / video generation</li><li><strong>Synthesia</strong> &mdash; https://www.synthesia.io &mdash; AI avatar video</li><li><strong>Fliki</strong> &mdash; https://fliki.ai &mdash; text-to-video / TTS</li><li><strong>Pictory</strong> &mdash; https://pictory.ai &mdash; video from text</li><li><strong>Squibler</strong> &mdash; https://www.squibler.io &mdash; AI script/novel writing</li><li><strong>Youbooks</strong> &mdash; https://www.youbooks.com &mdash; AI non-fiction book generator</li><li><strong>BookBud</strong> &mdash; https://www.bookbud.ai &mdash; AI book writer for self-publishers</li><li><strong>Murphy</strong> &mdash; https://murphy.inc &mdash; AI movie-script generator</li><li><strong>Melies AI</strong> &mdash; https://melies.co &mdash; AI screenplay writer</li><li><strong>Morphed</strong> &mdash; https://morphed.app &mdash; multi-model AI video generator</li><li><strong>FutureTools.io</strong> &mdash; https://www.futuretools.io &mdash; AI tool directory (Matt Wolfe's)</li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "creator-outreach",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "12.8"
    },
    "creator-outreach-priority": {
      "id": "creator-outreach-priority",
      "name": "Recommended Outreach Priority",
      "content": "<h3>Top of funnel first</h3><ol><li><strong>Jason Hamilton / The Nerdy Novelist</strong> &mdash; tightest workflow match; whole channel is \"AI for outlining + writing books.\"</li><li><strong>Curious Refuge (Caleb Ward)</strong> &mdash; the AI-filmmaking/screenwriting hub; outline &rarr; screenplay &rarr; narrated video is their world.</li><li><strong>Theoretically Media (Tim Simmons)</strong> &mdash; tool-review beat; primed to demo IdiamPro's pipeline.</li><li><strong>Joanna Penn</strong> &mdash; credibility + tasteful-AI framing for the authoring audience.</li><li><strong>Matt Wolfe</strong> &mdash; sheer reach for a single \"one idea &rarr; many outputs\" demo.</li></ol>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "creator-outreach",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "12.9"
    },
    "creator-outreach-gaps": {
      "id": "creator-outreach-gaps",
      "name": "Honest Gaps to Flag",
      "content": "<ul><li><strong>Diagrams / visual-thinking</strong> individual creators: no strong AI-native voice verified.</li><li><strong>Screenwriting-with-AI</strong> beyond Curious Refuge: dominated by tools, few creator-voices.</li><li><strong>EdTech-AI</strong> individual creators: mostly orgs/tools, not personal channels.</li><li>Several subscriber counts were deliberately omitted where unverifiable &mdash; confirm live before any public testimonial use.</li></ul>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "creator-outreach",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "12.10"
    },
    "creator-outreach-v5": {
      "id": "creator-outreach-v5",
      "name": "Julia McCoy",
      "content": "<p><strong>[HOWARD-FLAGGED &mdash; HIGH PRIORITY]</strong> (Howard named her personally.)</p><p><strong>Platform + URL:</strong> Founder &amp; CEO of First Movers &mdash; https://firstmovers.ai ; publishes on YouTube + the First Movers newsletter</p><p><strong>Covers:</strong> Teaches creators/entrepreneurs to build AI content systems and AI clones; famously trained a full AI clone/avatar of herself (voice, face, thinking) and runs it prolifically on YouTube.</p><p><strong>IdiamPro angle:</strong> Her audience is builders who want one person&rsquo;s ideas to scale into massive output &mdash; a word-for-word match to IdiamPro&rsquo;s \"one idea into many finished works.\" Ideal evangelist.</p>",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "creator-outreach-video",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "12.3.5"
    },
    "creator-outreach-email-template-v1": {
      "id": "creator-outreach-email-template-v1",
      "name": "Outreach Email — Template (v2)",
      "content": "<p>Subject: One idea → published to the whole planet, in any language, at any level</p><p>Hi [First Name],</p><p>I follow your work on [their focus], so you&#x27;ll understand why this matters — and you&#x27;ll be skeptical, which is exactly why I want you to be the one to judge it.</p><p>Last week I fed a single outline into IdiamPro. In about ten minutes it wrote a complete book — table of contents and every chapter. Ten minutes more, it became a podcast. Then a narrated video, with diagrams it generated on its own.</p><p>But here&#x27;s the part that stops people cold:</p><p>IdiamPro publishes the same idea multilingual, multilevel, and multimedia — any language, any level of understanding, any format. One book can speak to a Nobel laureate and to a curious six-year-old, in English or Mandarin or Portuguese, as text, audio, or video. Practically anyone on Earth over the age of two becomes a potential reader, listener, or viewer.</p><p>That&#x27;s not a note app — it&#x27;s a creative workstation that turns one person&#x27;s thinking into products the entire world can consume, and that creators and entrepreneurs can actually sell. The leverage is the whole point: a single mind can now produce, publish, and monetize at a scale that used to demand a full studio. AI is the most disruptive force of our lifetime, and IdiamPro is how one person harnesses it — I believe it will change how the public and professionals alike create, and let a lot of sharp people build real businesses, and real fortunes, doing it.</p><p>I&#x27;ve chased this idea for about 35 years. AI finally made it real.</p><p>You evaluate the best tools on the planet, so I&#x27;ll be direct: I think this belongs among them. Judge for yourself — secondbrainware.com.</p><p>If you&#x27;re open to evaluating it, I&#x27;ll set you up with early beta access, or a free copy of the full app — your choice, no strings. And if it earns your respect, we&#x27;d be proud to feature and promote you in return, with an ambassador program for creators who want to take it further.</p><p>Would you take a look?</p><p>Best,<br>Howard Jachter<br>Founder, IdiamPro — SecondBrainWare LLC</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "creator-outreach",
      "childrenIds": [
        "creator-outreach-email-template-v1-status"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": ""
    },
    "creator-outreach-email-template-v1-status": {
      "id": "creator-outreach-email-template-v1-status",
      "name": "Status & TODO",
      "content": "<p>STATUS: v2 draft, approved-in-direction by Howard 2026-07-14. WEBSITE URL: DONE — secondbrainware.com. TODO before send: (1) personalize opening line per recipient; (2) sending is Howard&#x27;s call. Amped per Howard: stress multilingual/multilevel/multimedia universal reach + monetization/leverage + disruptive vision, kept credible with the concrete 10-minute-book proof.</p>",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "creator-outreach-email-template-v1",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": ""
    },
    "51b3e21f-84b6-4f9f-98ad-3d7ade039d33": {
      "id": "51b3e21f-84b6-4f9f-98ad-3d7ade039d33",
      "name": "Pricing & Cost Analysis (confirmed 2026-07-16)",
      "content": "Confirmed launch pricing + the cost model behind it. Full write-up: standalone outline \"IdiamPro - Pricing & Cost Analysis\" and docs/pricing-cost-analysis.md.",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "root",
      "childrenIds": [
        "b136d890-1354-4a9d-a311-166abc783912",
        "3d287201-5cc8-4748-b158-38149e2d5482",
        "2d9d2dac-cc32-4fd9-bf13-7cd44e3138b3",
        "2deaae1e-a84e-45f3-af44-1b519acebc7b"
      ],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189095607,
        "updatedAt": 1784189095607
      }
    },
    "b136d890-1354-4a9d-a311-166abc783912": {
      "id": "b136d890-1354-4a9d-a311-166abc783912",
      "name": "Confirmed tiers",
      "content": "Free: $0 forever (core app + on-device Google Gemma AI).\nProfessional: $19.99/mo on web & Mac ($29.99/mo on iPhone/iPad, via the App Store, to cover Apple's cut). First month free.\nStudent: $9.99/mo (half price) on web & Mac ($14.99 iPhone/iPad); verify with a .edu email; lighter premium allowance so the discount stays cash-positive.",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "51b3e21f-84b6-4f9f-98ad-3d7ade039d33",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189095607,
        "updatedAt": 1784189095607
      }
    },
    "3d287201-5cc8-4748-b158-38149e2d5482": {
      "id": "3d287201-5cc8-4748-b158-38149e2d5482",
      "name": "Method — 20% margin, calculated backwards",
      "content": "Margin = 20% share of the SALE PRICE, over FULLY-LOADED cost (AI allowance + infra/overhead + payment fee). Price = cost / (1 - margin - payment-fee rate). Web fee ~3% (Stripe); iPhone 15-30% (Apple IAP). Never below cost; usage metered so cost can't run away. Uses industry-standard cost inputs until real vendor figures are known.",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "51b3e21f-84b6-4f9f-98ad-3d7ade039d33",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189095607,
        "updatedAt": 1784189095607
      }
    },
    "2d9d2dac-cc32-4fd9-bf13-7cd44e3138b3": {
      "id": "2d9d2dac-cc32-4fd9-bf13-7cd44e3138b3",
      "name": "The value anchor",
      "content": "$20/month is the floor for any serious LLM subscription (ChatGPT Plus, Claude Pro, Gemini Advanced are all $20). IdiamPro Professional at $19.99 = the price of one bare chatbot, with the whole thinking system on top (outlining, consolidation, Second Brain, and every finished output). A genuine deal for the customer; cash-positive for us.",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "51b3e21f-84b6-4f9f-98ad-3d7ade039d33",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189095607,
        "updatedAt": 1784189095607
      }
    },
    "2deaae1e-a84e-45f3-af44-1b519acebc7b": {
      "id": "2deaae1e-a84e-45f3-af44-1b519acebc7b",
      "name": "Optional add-on revenue lines",
      "content": "All priced at the same 20% margin: overage top-up packs (when the monthly allowance runs out), premium-voice upgrade, BYOK discount path (bring your own key = lower price), annual billing (~2 months free).",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "51b3e21f-84b6-4f9f-98ad-3d7ade039d33",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1784189095607,
        "updatedAt": 1784189095607
      }
    }
  },
